<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870622-0037 </DOCNO><HL> Supreme Equipment Holding</HL><DD> 06/22/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SEQPTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Towle andamp; Co., a St. Louis, Mo.-based investment advisory concern, said it holds a 5.1% stake for its clients in Supreme Equipment andamp; Systems Corp.'s common shares outstanding.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission, Towle said it holds 55,900 common shares of the New York-based maker and marketer of filing cabinets and storage systems. Officials at Supreme weren't available for comment.    J. Ellwood Towle, Towle's president, said the stake is strictly an investment. &quot;We believe it's an undervalued situation,&quot; he said. </TEXT></DOC>